New Records: Shohei Ohtani became the first player in 23 years to reach 400 total bases in a season.
Key Match Events: Freddie Freeman's sprained ankle will end his regular season, but he should be available for the NLDS.
Walker Buehler allowed just one run in five innings, keeping the Dodgers in the game.
Will Smith hit a game-tying home run off Joe Musgrove.
Mookie Betts hit a two-run single to extend the Dodgers' lead.
Shohei Ohtani's single gave the Dodgers the lead in the seventh inning.
Pre-Game Insights: The Dodgers needed to claim a series for the right to celebrate with fans in their own ballpark for the first time since 2018.
Post-Match Reflections: Freddie Freeman expressed determination to be ready for the NLDS despite his sprained ankle.
Dave Roberts noted that this division win felt 'a tick sweeter' due to the challenges faced throughout the season.
Walker Buehler reflected on his return to pitching in big games after undergoing a second Tommy John surgery.
Max Muncy praised Walker Buehler's ability to perform in big situations.
Mookie Betts expressed excitement and relief after contributing to the win.
Shohei Ohtani expressed eagerness to continue celebrating with the team.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dodgers celebrated their NL West win with a traditional tequila toast and champagne celebration.
Shohei Ohtani's recent performance has been outstanding, going 20-for-29 with five homers and seven stolen bases over his last seven games.
